						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar lying in the Sagarēśvara Svāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1254 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1176, Uttarāyaṇasankrānti, corresponding to 1254 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 55 sheep <hi rend="italic">(goṟiyalu)</hi> for maintaining the perpetual lamp in the temple of Sakalēśvara mahādēva by Mārebōya for the merit of his parents Gōnajavrōli Nannebōya and mother (name not mentioned).</p>						

						</summary>
